{
  "texts": [
    "The integration of Internet of Things (IoT) technologies into agriculture has catalyzed a paradigm shift, revolutionizing efficiency, productivity, and sustainability in farming systems.",
    "IoT applications, including precision farming, smart irrigation, and livestock monitoring, have demonstrated tangible benefits such as increased crop yields (up to 20%), reduced water use (8%), and lower energy costs (13%), enhancing both economic viability and environmental stewardship.",
    "Advanced IoT devices like soil sensors, drones, and climate control systems are empowering farmers to adopt data-driven approaches, optimize resource allocation, and boost global market access.",
    "Despite these advancements, challenges like integration complexity, cybersecurity, and scalability remain critical barriers.",
    "Addressing these requires multidisciplinary research and the development of robust frame- Regulatory and government policies are crucial for protecting farmers' rights and supporting their adoption of these technologies."
  ]
}